The Telegraph - Calcutta : Sports

 Chowrasia aims to build lead 

A STAFF REPORTER

Calcutta: Having made a perfect start to the 2006-07 season on the Professional Golf Tour of India (PGTI) with a winner and runner-up finish in the first two events, SSP Chowrasia is eyeing to build his lead in the order of merit with a victory at the Rs.5000,000 EMAAR-MGF PGTI Championship to be held at the Karnataka Golf Association, Bangalore from December 19-22, according to information received here. 

The city golfer is scheduled to play the Volvo Masters in Thailand next week but will fly back directly to Bangalore to play the EMAAR-MGF PGTI Championship. quot;There is no reason I should not play well as I am confident of my form and am really looking forward to playing this event, quot; Chowrasia said. 

Winner of the 2006 Taiwan Masters, Gaurav Ghei; Harmeet Kahlon, Uttam Singh Mundy, Digvijay Singh, Amandeep Johl, Vivek Bhandari, Naman Dawar and Amritinder Singh, among others, will vie for top honours . 




